sheIgmpMib.name: sheIgmpMib

revisions.description: Change the sheIgmpNotifications to sheIgmpNotification. The first name is duplicated with the object defined in she-bridge-mib
Bring them to common SHE MIB package with R2.8.
Correct description for sheIgmpPreviewPackageChannelList. Correct index values for sheIgmpSubscriberTable.
Update for SHE R2.8. Add controlrequest and controlgroup parameter for set sheIgmpLongTimeOnlineTime.

sheIgmpMib.description: The MIB module is to describe managed objects supporting additional IGMP features.

sheIgmpProgramPreviewEnable.name: sheIgmpProgramPreviewEnable
sheIgmpProgramPreviewEnable.description: Indicates whether to enable the program preview functionality.

sheIgmpLogEnable.name: sheIgmpLogEnable
sheIgmpLogEnable.description: Whether the NE should keep the IGMP log.

sheIgmpUploadEnable.name: sheIgmpUploadEnable
sheIgmpUploadEnable.description: Whether the NE should upload the log files to FTP server.

sheIgmpFtpRootDir.name: sheIgmpFtpRootDir
sheIgmpFtpRootDir.description: The root directory name on FTP server that stores the IGMP log data of this DSLAM. It is the relative path to the ftproot, eg. 'hix5635/v1.5/dslam1/igmp' The directory structure looks like: ftproot <-- the upmost ftp root |- %FtpRootDir% <-- this value, specifies the DSLAM

sheIgmpFtpUser.name: sheIgmpFtpUser
sheIgmpFtpUser.description: FTP user name. Write permission is required for this user.

sheIgmpFtpPassword.name: sheIgmpFtpPassword
sheIgmpFtpPassword.description: FTP server access password. To protect the password, the string of this object in the GetResponse PDU is encrypted.

sheIgmpFtpUploadInterval.name: sheIgmpFtpUploadInterval
sheIgmpFtpUploadInterval.description: The interval that IGMP log data is uploaded to FTP server.

sheIgmpPacketRateLimitUplink.name: sheIgmpPacketRateLimitUplink
sheIgmpPacketRateLimitUplink.description: IGMP packets received from the uplink port is only allowed to be processed by the IGMP proxy with a limit of this value per minute. -1 is a special value means no limit.

sheIgmpPacketRateLimitSubscriber.name: sheIgmpPacketRateLimitSubscriber
sheIgmpPacketRateLimitSubscriber.description: IGMP packets received from the DSL subscriber port is only allowed to be processed by the IGMP proxy with a limit of this value per minute. -1 is a special value means no limit.

sheIgmpLongTimeOnlineTime.name: sheIgmpLongTimeOnlineTime
sheIgmpLongTimeOnlineTime.description: For every time interval of this value, there should be a log entry sent to the FTP server for those subscribers who have joined a multicast group for more than this time interval.

sheIgmpEthernetAccessEnable.name: sheIgmpEthernetAccessEnable
sheIgmpEthernetAccessEnable.description: When sheIgmpEthernetAccessEnable is true, if ethernet port of the CxU is configured as aggregate, multicast traffic could be accessed only if there's IGMP report sent from it. When sheIgmpEthernetAccessEnable is false, if ethernet port of the CxU is configured as aggregate, multicast traffic could be accessed without IGMP report.

sheIgmpControlRequest.name: sheIgmpControlRequest
sheIgmpControlRequest.description: Command to configure global system parameters. It must be the last member in the varBindList of the SNMP set request. The parameters for different commands are listed below: setIgmpParameters: (optional, but at least one of them should be there) sheIgmpControlProgramPreviewEnable sheIgmpControlLogEnable sheIgmpControlUploadEnable setFtpParameters: sheIgmpControlFtpRootDir sheIgmpControlFtpIp sheIgmpControlFtpUser sheIgmpControlFtpPassword sheIgmpControlFtpUploadInterval setIgmpPacketRateLimitUplink: sheIgmpControlPacketRateLimitUplink setIgmpPacketRateLimitSubscriber: sheIgmpControlPacketRateLimitSubscriber setIgmpLongTimeOnlineTime: sheIgmpControlLongTimeOnlineTime setIgmpEthernetAccessEnable: sheIgmpControlEthernetAccessEnable resetSubscriberPreviewCountAll: manuallyUploadLog: (no parameter) Notifications: sheIgmpControlResult at the command ending in case of long running command. The long running command refers to the case that sheIgmpUploadEnable is changed from disable to enable. NE will verify the FTP connection at the enabling moment. Besides, the RootDir is created if they do not exist yet. EM should GET sheIgmpControlReqResult when the Response of the SET PDU is received, and the error status is noError. If the value of sheIgmpControlReqResult is comExecStarted(30), which means the SET operation is a long running command, EM must issue another GET operation on sheIgmpControlTimer. A timer should start on EM with the expire time equals to the value of sheIgmpControlTimer. The sheIgmpControlResult trap is expected to reach EM within the specified time. When the trap is received by EM, EM can optionally GET sheIgmpControlReqResult, sheIgmpControlStatus, and sheIgmpControlTimeStamp.

sheIgmpControlStatus.name: sheIgmpControlStatus
sheIgmpControlStatus.description: The status of a control request.

sheIgmpControlTimer.name: sheIgmpControlTimer
sheIgmpControlTimer.description: The maximum wait time for the manager for command ending. For long running commands. The manager reads this value from the SHE.

sheIgmpControlReqResult.name: sheIgmpControlReqResult
sheIgmpControlReqResult.description: The result of the last user command.

sheIgmpControlTimeStamp.name: sheIgmpControlTimeStamp
sheIgmpControlTimeStamp.description: The time stamp of the last command (end of command).

sheIgmpControlProgramPreviewEnable.name: sheIgmpControlProgramPreviewEnable
sheIgmpControlProgramPreviewEnable.description: Indicates whether to enable the program preview functionality.

sheIgmpControlLogEnable.name: sheIgmpControlLogEnable
sheIgmpControlLogEnable.description: Whether the NE should keep the IGMP log. Change the value of sheIgmpLogEnable.

sheIgmpControlUploadEnable.name: sheIgmpControlUploadEnable
sheIgmpControlUploadEnable.description: Whether the FTP upload process is enabled. Change the value of sheIgmpUploadEnable. If the sheIgmpUploadEnable is changed from disable to enable, FTP connection will be verified at the enabling moment. Besides, the RootDir is created if they do not exist yet. The command in this case is a long running command. sheIgmpControlResult trap will be sent to EM to notify the command result.

sheIgmpControlFtpRootDir.name: sheIgmpControlFtpRootDir
sheIgmpControlFtpRootDir.description: The root directory name on FTP server that stores the IGMP log data of this DSLAM. Change the value of sheIgmpFtpRootDir.

sheIgmpControlFtpIp.name: sheIgmpControlFtpIp
sheIgmpControlFtpIp.description: FTP server's IP address. Change the value of sheIgmpFtpIp.

sheIgmpControlFtpUser.name: sheIgmpControlFtpUser
sheIgmpControlFtpUser.description: FTP user name. Change the value of sheIgmpFtpUser.

sheIgmpControlFtpPassword.name: sheIgmpControlFtpPassword
sheIgmpControlFtpPassword.description: FTP server access password. To protect the password, the string of this object in the GetResponse PDU is encrypted.

sheIgmpControlFtpUploadInterval.name: sheIgmpControlFtpUploadInterval
sheIgmpControlFtpUploadInterval.description: The interval that IGMP log data is uploaded to FTP server. Change the value of sheIgmpFtpUploadInterval.

sheIgmpControlPacketRateLimitSubscriber.name: sheIgmpControlPacketRateLimitSubscriber
sheIgmpControlPacketRateLimitSubscriber.description: IGMP packets received from the DSL subscriber port is only allowed to be processed by the IGMP proxy with a limit of this value per minute. -1 is a special value means no limit.

sheIgmpControlPacketRateLimitUplink.name: sheIgmpControlPacketRateLimitUplink
sheIgmpControlPacketRateLimitUplink.description: IGMP packets received from the uplink port is only allowed to be processed by the IGMP proxy with a limit of this value per minute. -1 is a special value means no limit.

sheIgmpControlLongTimeOnlineTime.name: sheIgmpControlLongTimeOnlineTime
sheIgmpControlLongTimeOnlineTime.description: For every time interval of this value, there should be a log entry sent to the FTP server for those subscribers who have joined a multicast group for more than this time interval.

sheIgmpControlEthernetAccessEnable.name: sheIgmpControlEthernetAccessEnable
sheIgmpControlEthernetAccessEnable.description: When sheIgmpEthernetAccessEnable is true, if ethernet port of the CxU is configured as aggregate, multicast traffic could be accessed only if there's IGMP report sent from it. When sheIgmpEthernetAccessEnable is false, if ethernet port of the CxU is configured as aggregate, multicast traffic could be accessed without IGMP report.

sheIgmpPreviewPackageTable.name: sheIgmpPreviewPackageTable
sheIgmpPreviewPackageTable.description: This table contains information of preview packages. Each entry defines a preview package.

sheIgmpPreviewPackageIndex.name: sheIgmpPreviewPackageIndex
sheIgmpPreviewPackageIndex.description: The index of the preview package.

sheIgmpPreviewPackageDescription.name: sheIgmpPreviewPackageDescription
sheIgmpPreviewPackageDescription.description: The description of this preview package.

sheIgmpPreviewPackageLastingPeriod.name: sheIgmpPreviewPackageLastingPeriod
sheIgmpPreviewPackageLastingPeriod.description: The duration (in minutes) for each preview period.

sheIgmpPreviewPackageIntervalBetweenPrev.name: sheIgmpPreviewPackageIntervalBetweenPreviews
sheIgmpPreviewPackageIntervalBetweenPrev.description: The time that a user must wait before starting next preview.

sheIgmpPreviewPackageMaxPreviewsNum.name: sheIgmpPreviewPackageMaxPreviewsNum
sheIgmpPreviewPackageMaxPreviewsNum.description: How many previews are allowed on a subscriber.

sheIgmpPreviewPackageChannelList.name: sheIgmpPreviewPackageChannelList
sheIgmpPreviewPackageChannelList.description: The list of pairs of octets each identifying a corresponding index of the sheIgmpGroupTable (sheIgmpGroupIndex). It shows the channels that are members of this preview package. The least significant byte is the second octet.

sheIgmpPreviewPackageControlRequest.name: sheIgmpPreviewPackageControlRequest
sheIgmpPreviewPackageControlRequest.description: Command to configure preview package. It must be the last member in the varBindList of the SNMP set request. The parameters for different commands are listed below: createPreviewPackage: sheIgmpPreviewPackageControlLastingPeriod sheIgmpPreviewPackageControlIntervalBetweenPreviews sheIgmpPreviewPackageControlMaxPreviewsNum (optional) sheIgmpPreviewPackageControlDescription deletePreviewPackage: sheIgmpPreviewPackageControlIndex modifyPreviewPackage: (must) sheIgmpPreviewPackageControlIndex (optional, but at least one of them should be there) sheIgmpPreviewPackageControlLastingPeriod sheIgmpPreviewPackageControlIntervalBetweenPreviews sheIgmpPreviewPackageControlMaxPreviewsNum sheIgmpPreviewPackageControlDescription addChannel2PreviewPackage: deleteChannelFromPreviewPackage: sheIgmpPreviewPackageControlIndex sheIgmpPreviewPackageControlChannelIndex

sheIgmpPreviewPackageControlStatus.name: sheIgmpPreviewPackageControlStatus
sheIgmpPreviewPackageControlStatus.description: The status of a user command.

sheIgmpPreviewPackageControlTimer.name: sheIgmpPreviewPackageControlTimer
sheIgmpPreviewPackageControlTimer.description: The maximum wait time for the manager for a long running user command.

sheIgmpPreviewPackageControlReqResult.name: sheIgmpPreviewPackageControlReqResult
sheIgmpPreviewPackageControlReqResult.description: The result of the last user command.

sheIgmpPreviewPackageControlTimeStamp.name: sheIgmpPreviewPackageControlTimeStamp
sheIgmpPreviewPackageControlTimeStamp.description: The time stamp of the last command (end of command).

sheIgmpPreviewPackageControlIndex.name: sheIgmpPreviewPackageControlIndex
sheIgmpPreviewPackageControlIndex.description: The index of the preview package.

sheIgmpPreviewPackageControlLastingPerio.name: sheIgmpPreviewPackageControlLastingPeriod
sheIgmpPreviewPackageControlLastingPerio.description: The duration (in minutes) for each preview period.

sheIgmpPreviewPackageControlIntervalBetw.name: sheIgmpPreviewPackageControlIntervalBetweenPreviews
sheIgmpPreviewPackageControlIntervalBetw.description: The time that a user must wait before starting next preview.

sheIgmpPreviewPackageControlMaxPreviewsN.name: sheIgmpPreviewPackageControlMaxPreviewsNum
sheIgmpPreviewPackageControlMaxPreviewsN.description: How many previews are allowed on a subscriber.

sheIgmpPreviewPackageControlChannelIndex.name: sheIgmpPreviewPackageControlChannelIndex
sheIgmpPreviewPackageControlChannelIndex.description: The channel index that will be added to or deleted from the preview package. The value will be equal to an existing sheIgmpGroupIndex from sheBridgeMib, which represent an IgmpChannel.

sheIgmpSubscriberTable.name: sheIgmpSubscriberTable
sheIgmpSubscriberTable.description: Each entry in this table defines the multicast parameters for a subscriber.

sheIgmpSubscriberEntry.name: sheIgmpSubscriberEntry
sheIgmpSubscriberEntry.description: Entry of the table indeced by sheBridgePortIndex. The sheBridgePortIndex is an external index defined in she-bridge-mib.

sheIgmpSubscriberPreviewPackageIndex.name: sheIgmpSubscriberPreviewPackageIndex
sheIgmpSubscriberPreviewPackageIndex.description: The index of the preview package that is applied on this subscriber. 0 means no package assigned.

sheIgmpSubscriberPreviewRemains.name: sheIgmpSubscriberPreviewRemains
sheIgmpSubscriberPreviewRemains.description: The number of previews that are still available on this subscriber currently. The initial value of this object equals to sheIgmpPreviewPackageMaxPreviewsNum. It decreases by 1 each time when the subscriber starts a preview. If this number reaches 0, this subscriber cannot preview any more, unless this counter is reset by EM.

sheIgmpSubscriberControlRequest.name: sheIgmpSubscriberControlRequest
sheIgmpSubscriberControlRequest.description: Command to configure subscriber parameters. It must be the last member in the varBindList of the SNMP set request. The parameters for different commands are listed below: (must) sheIgmpSubscriberControlIndex setSubscriberPreviewPackage: sheIgmpSubscriberControlPreviewPackageIndex deleteSubscriberPreviewPackage: resetSubscriberPreviewRemainsCount: (no additional parameters)

sheIgmpSubscriberControlStatus.name: sheIgmpSubscriberControlStatus
sheIgmpSubscriberControlStatus.description: The status of a user command.

sheIgmpSubscriberControlTimer.name: sheIgmpSubscriberControlTimer
sheIgmpSubscriberControlTimer.description: The maximum wait time for the manager for a long running user command.

sheIgmpSubscriberControlReqResult.name: sheIgmpSubscriberControlReqResult
sheIgmpSubscriberControlReqResult.description: The result of the last user command.

sheIgmpSubscriberControlTimeStamp.name: sheIgmpSubscriberControlTimeStamp
sheIgmpSubscriberControlTimeStamp.description: The time stamp of the last command (end of command).

sheIgmpSubscriberControlIndex.name: sheIgmpSubscriberControlIndex
sheIgmpSubscriberControlIndex.description: The sheBridgePortIndex to identify a subscriber.

sheIgmpSubscriberControlPreviewPackageIn.name: sheIgmpSubscriberControlPreviewPackageIndex
sheIgmpSubscriberControlPreviewPackageIn.description: The index of the preview package that is applied on this subscriber.

sheIgmpLastUploadStatus.name: sheIgmpLastUploadStatus
sheIgmpLastUploadStatus.description: The status of last FTP upload operation. It could be uploadSuccess(1) or uploadFail(2).

sheIgmpLastUploadTimeStamp.name: sheIgmpLastUploadTimeStamp
sheIgmpLastUploadTimeStamp.description: The time stamp of the last FTP upload operation (end of operation).

sheIgmpLastUploadFileName.name: sheIgmpLastUploadFileName
sheIgmpLastUploadFileName.description: The file name of last FTP upload operation.

sheIgmpLastUploadErrorString.name: sheIgmpLastUploadErrorString
sheIgmpLastUploadErrorString.description: The text that describes the FTP upload failure. If upload succeeded, this string is empty.

sheIgmpControlResult.name: sheIgmpControlResult
sheIgmpControlResult.description: Notification sent at the end of long running command. The possible values of sheIgmpControlReqResult are: wrongIpAddress(2), -- IP address of FTP server is incorrect wrongUserPassword(3), -- The user name or password is wrong permissionDenied(4), -- The user name has no permission to create dir/file commandSucceeded(37), commandFailed(36)

sheIgmpUploadFailedTrap.name: sheIgmpUploadFailedTrap
sheIgmpUploadFailedTrap.description: Indicates that an FTP upload failure occurred.

sheIgmpPreviewPackageControlResult.name: sheIgmpPreviewPackageControlResult
sheIgmpPreviewPackageControlResult.description: Notification sent at the end of preview package command.

sheIgmpParaV2CDRTime.name: sheIgmpParaV2CDRTime
sheIgmpParaV2CDRTime.description: This attribute indicates the value of CDR Recognition Time. Value 0 means user doesn't configure IGMP Log CDR Time and IGMP Log CDR process doesn't take effect.

sheIgmpParaV2ControlRequest.name: sheIgmpParaV2ControlRequest
sheIgmpParaV2ControlRequest.description: It must be the last member in the varBindList of the SNMP set request. The commands: setIgmpCDRTime The parameter for this command is sheIgmpParaV2ControlCDRTime.

sheIgmpParaV2ControlStatus.name: sheIgmpParaV2ControlStatus
sheIgmpParaV2ControlStatus.description: The status of a control request.

sheIgmpParaV2ControlTimer.name: sheIgmpParaV2ControlTimer
sheIgmpParaV2ControlTimer.description: The maximum wait time for the manager for command ending. For long running commands. The manager reads this value from the SHE.

sheIgmpParaV2ControlReqResult.name: sheIgmpParaV2ControlReqResult
sheIgmpParaV2ControlReqResult.description: The result of the last user command.

sheIgmpParaV2ControlTimeStamp.name: sheIgmpParaV2ControlTimeStamp
sheIgmpParaV2ControlTimeStamp.description: The time stamp of the last command (end of command).

sheIgmpParaV2ControlCDRTime.name: sheIgmpParaV2ControlCDRTime
sheIgmpParaV2ControlCDRTime.description: This attribute indicates the value of CDR recognition time. Value 0 means user doesn't configure IGMP Log CDR Time and IGMP Log CDR process doesn't take effect.

sheIgmpMulticastChannelTable.name: sheIgmpMulticastChannelTable
sheIgmpMulticastChannelTable.description: This table contains information for the Bandwidth assigned to every Multicast Group.

sheIgmpMulticastChannelEntry.name: sheIgmpMulticastChannelEntry
sheIgmpMulticastChannelEntry.description: Each entry contains the configured bandwidth value of a Multicast Group. The sheIgmpGroupIndex is an external index defined in she-bridge-mib.

sheIgmpMulticastChannelDelayLeaveTime.name: sheIgmpMulticastChannelDelayLeaveTime
sheIgmpMulticastChannelDelayLeaveTime.description: Time interval for which the IGMP proxy 's host will delay to send a leave to the Router side when no membership is in a multicast channel.

sheIgmpMulticastChannelControlRequest.name: sheIgmpMulticastChannelControlRequest
sheIgmpMulticastChannelControlRequest.description: Command to set multicast channel delay leave time. It must be the last member in the varBindList of the SNMP set request. The commands: setIgmpSetMulticastChannelV2Para The Parameters of this command are sheIgmpMulticastChannelControlChannelIndex sheIgmpMulticastChannelControlDelayLeaveTime

sheIgmpMulticastChannelControlStatus.name: sheIgmpMulticastChannelControlStatus
sheIgmpMulticastChannelControlStatus.description: The status of a control request.

sheIgmpMulticastChannelControlReqResult.name: sheIgmpMulticastChannelControlReqResult
sheIgmpMulticastChannelControlReqResult.description: The result of the last user command.

sheIgmpMulticastChannelControlTimeStamp.name: sheIgmpMulticastChannelControlTimeStamp
sheIgmpMulticastChannelControlTimeStamp.description: The time stamp of the last command (end of command).

sheIgmpMulticastChannelControlChannelInd.name: sheIgmpMulticastChannelControlChannelIndex
sheIgmpMulticastChannelControlChannelInd.description: This attribute indicates the index of the multicast group being configured.

sheIgmpMulticastChannelControlDelayLeave.name: sheIgmpMulticastChannelControlDelayLeaveTime
sheIgmpMulticastChannelControlDelayLeave.description: Time interval for which the IGMP proxy 's host will delay to send a leave to the Router side when no membership is in a multicast channel.

sheIgmpPreviewV2ParaARTEnable.name: sheIgmpPreviewV2ParaARTEnable
sheIgmpPreviewV2ParaARTEnable.description: This attribute indicates whether the preview auto reset time functionlaity is enabled.

sheIgmpPreviewV2ParaARTStartTime.name: sheIgmpPreviewV2ParaARTStartTime
sheIgmpPreviewV2ParaARTStartTime.description: This attribute indicates the start time of auto reset timer.

sheIgmpPreviewV2ParaARTUnit.name: sheIgmpPreviewV2ParaARTUnit
sheIgmpPreviewV2ParaARTUnit.description: This attribute indicates the unit of the timer.

sheIgmpPreviewV2ParaARTValue.name: sheIgmpPreviewV2ParaARTValue
sheIgmpPreviewV2ParaARTValue.description: This attribute indicates the configured value of the preview auto reset timer. The timer value will be decided together by sheIgmpPreviewAutoResetTimeValue and the sheIgmpPreviewAutoResetTimeUnit. e.g. if the sheIgmpPreviewAutoResetTimeUnit is day(1) and the sheIgmpPreviewAutoResetTimeValue is 30 then the value of auto reset timer is 30 days.

sheIgmpPreviewV2ParaControlRequest.name: sheIgmpPreviewV2ParaControlRequest
sheIgmpPreviewV2ParaControlRequest.description: Command related to the preview auto reset time. It must be the last member in the varBindList of the SNMP set request. The commands: setIgmpPreviewAutoResetTimeEnable The parameters for this command are sheIgmpPreviewV2ParaControlARTStartTime sheIgmpPreviewV2ParaControlARTEnable sheIgmpPreviewV2ParaControlARTUnit sheIgmpPreviewV2ParaControlARTValue

sheIgmpPreviewV2ParaControlStatus.name: sheIgmpPreviewV2ParaControlStatus
sheIgmpPreviewV2ParaControlStatus.description: The status of a control request.

sheIgmpPreviewV2ParaControlTimeStamp.description: The time stamp of the last command (end of command).

sheIgmpPreviewV2ParaControlARTEnable.name: sheIgmpPreviewV2ParaControlARTEnable
sheIgmpPreviewV2ParaControlARTEnable.description: This attribute indicates whether the preview auto reset is enabled

sheIgmpPreviewV2ParaControlARTStartTime.name: sheIgmpPreviewV2ParaControlARTStartTime
sheIgmpPreviewV2ParaControlARTStartTime.description: This attribute indicates the start time of the auto reset timer

sheIgmpPreviewV2ParaControlARTUnit.name: sheIgmpPreviewV2ParaControlARTUnit
sheIgmpPreviewV2ParaControlARTUnit.description: This attribute indicates the unit of the preview auto reset timer

sheIgmpPreviewV2ParaControlARTValue.name: sheIgmpPreviewV2ParaControlARTValue
